# Caching

**This project does not use Redis or in-memory cache by default.**

## Rules

- Do not introduce caching layers unless explicitly requested
- Do not cache auth/session data in shared cache without invalidation strategy
- Never cache per-user data in global cache without user-scoped keys

## When caching is added

- Define TTL and invalidation on every write path
- Cache keys: `{entity}:{id}` or `{entity}:list:{hash}`
- Prefer cache-aside pattern
- Document in module README comment

## Never cache

- JWT validation results bypassing DB session check
- Password hashes or tokens
- Non-idempotent POST responses

Until requested, rely on PostgreSQL query optimization and pagination.
